50|$|Founded in 1946 by Stephen A. Brooks, Brooks Instrument was {{originally}} based in Lansdale, Pennsylvania. The company {{was built on}} the strength of an innovative side-plate, <b>dowel-pin</b> principle of rotameter construction, which is, today, the basis of one of the company's more important product lines. In 1958 the company developed a new, streamlined laboratory flow meter named Sho-Rate and a new type of full-view rotameter - with an improved packaging seal that represents one of the first innovations for the glass tube rotameter in 20 years.|$|E

